(45, 61, 2, 'Foundations of Finance & Excel', '1 Microsoft Excel for Finance & IB\r\n1.1 Excel Interface & Navigation, Master Keyboard Shortcuts, Rows, Columns, Tabs, Sheets, Cells, Workbook Organization\r\n1.2 Essential Formulas - SUM, AVERAGE, COUNT, MIN, MAX, ABS, ROUND, SUMIF, COUNTIF, SUMPRODUCT, etc. Date &\r\nTime Functions (TODAY, NOW, EDATE, EOMONTH, etc.)\r\n1.3 Conditional Logic & Lookup Functions - IF, IFERROR, AND, OR, VLOOKUP, HLOOKUP, XLOOKUP, INDEX, MATCH, etc.\r\n1.4 Formatting & Presentation - Investment Banking conventions (Inputs = Blue, Formulas = Black, Links = Green), Custom Number\r\nFormats, Borders, Font Consistency, Professional Cell Layout\r\n1.5 Data Cleaning & Preprocessing - Handling Missing Data, Removing Duplicates & Data Validation, and Text Functions (LEFT,\r\nRIGHT, MID, LEN, TRIM, UPPER, LOWER, PROPER, etc.)\r\n1.6 Financial Modeling Foundations - Create assumptions section (Revenue, Growth Rate, Tax, Margins), Link Values Dynamically\r\n(No Hardcoding), Build a Clean Table for Revenue Projections, Cost Breakdown, and Operating Profit Calculations.\r\n1.7 Basic Visualization - Bar Chart, Line Chart, Pie Chart, Waterfall Charts, Dynamic Charts, etc.\r\n1.8 Scenario & Sensitivity Tools - Data Tables (1-variable & 2-variable for DCF sensitivity), Goal Seek (e.g., find growth rate to\r\nhit target valuation), Toggle Switches for cases (best / worst / base).\r\n1.9 Pivot Tables & Data Aggregation - Creating Pivot Tables & Pivot Charts, Advanced Filtering with Slicers & Timelines, Grouping\r\nData, Calculated Fields & Custom Aggregations', '2025-05-31 15:33:35', '2025-05-31 15:33:35'),
(46, 61, 2, 'Accounting & Financial Fundamentals', '2.1 Understanding the 3 Financial Statements\r\n2.1.1 Income Statement (Profit and Loss) - Revenue, COGS, Gross Profit, Operating Expenses (SG&A, R&D) EBITDA, EBIT\r\n(Operating Profit), Net Income\r\n2.1.2 Balance Sheet - Assets (Current & Non-Current), Liabilities (Current & Long-term), Equity (Common Stock, Retained\r\nEarnings, etc.)\r\n2.1.3 Cash Flow Statement - Operating, Investing, Financing Activities, Indirect Method (Reconciliation from Net Income)\r\n2.2 Key Accounting Principles (GAAP / IFRS Basics) - Accrual vs Cash Accounting, Revenue Recognition, Matching Principle,\r\nDepreciation & Amortization, Capitalizing vs Expensing.\r\n2.3 Interlinking the 3 Statements - How Net Income flows into Retained Earnings, How Changes in Working Capital affect Cash\r\nFlow, How Depreciation reduces Net Income but increases Cash.\r\n2.4 Working Capital - Components (Inventory, Receivables, Payables), Changes in working capital and their impact on cash flow.\r\n2.5 Common Financial Ratios - Profitability, Liquidity, Efficiency, Leverage.\r\n2.6 Vertical Analysis - Expressing each line item as a % of revenue (P&L), Horizontal Analysis - year over year growth (% change\r\nover time)\r\n2.7 Deferred Taxes & Non-Cash Items\r\n2.8 DuPont Analysis, Free Cash Flow Analysis (Unlevered Free Cash Flow) & Trend Analysis\r\n2.9 Accounting Red Flags (IB Due Diligence Prep) - Revenue Manipulation, Aggressive Capitalization, Unusual expense timing or\r\nClassification.', '2025-05-31 15:33:35', '2025-05-31 15:33:35'),
(47, 61, 2, 'Financial Modeling & Valuation', '1 Financial Modeling Basics\r\n1.1 Modeling Fundamentals - What is a financial Model? What is it used in IB?, Types of models: 3-statement model, DCF, LBO,\r\nM&A, etc., IB modeling standards.\r\n1.2 Model Building Workflow - Revenue growth, margin %, tax rate, CapEx, etc., Build revenue and cost projections, Create\r\nsupporting schedules.\r\n1.3 Income Statement Forecasting - Project Revenue, COGS, Gross Profit, Operating expenses, EBITDA, Depreciation, Interest,\r\nTaxes, Net Income\r\n1.4 Balance Sheet Forecasting - Assets (Cash, AR, Inventory, PPE), Liabilities (Payables, Debt), Equity (Retained Earnings (linked\r\nto Net Income)).\r\n1.5 Cash Flow Statement - Net Income, Non-cash items (Depreciation, Amortization), Adjust for changes in working capital,\r\nInclude CapEx, debt changes, equity flows.\r\n1.6 Linking the 3 Statements - Net Income, Depreciation, Cash.\r\n1.7 Validation & Error Checks - Balance Sheet balances (Assets = Liabilities + Equity), Circular references, Build an error-check\r\nsection', '2025-05-31 15:33:35', '2025-05-31 15:33:35'),
(48, 61, 2, 'Core Valuation Analysis', '2.1 Discount Cash Flow (DCF)\r\n2.1.1 Overview of DCF - What is DCF and why it\'s used in IB?, Situations where DCF is most appropriate, Key Assumptions\r\nand Inputs required.\r\n2.1.2 Unlevered Free Cash Flow (UFCF) - Formula, EBIT vs. EBITDA, Treatment of non-cash items, Changes in working\r\ncapital (and why they matter), Projecting UFCFs over 5–10 years.\r\n2.1.3\r\nDiscount Rate (WACC) - Cost of Equity (CAPM Formula, Risk-free rate, Beta, Market risk premium), Cost of Debt\r\n(Pre-tax and after-tax cost of debt, Use of yield on debt or interest expense / total debt). Capital Structure\r\n(Target debt/equity ratio)\r\n2.1.4 Terminal Value - Gordon Growth Method, Exit Multiple Method.\r\n2.1.5 Present Value Calculations - Each year’s UFCF to present value using WACC, Terminal value to Present value.\r\n2.1.6 From Enterprise Value to Equity Value - Adjust for: Net debt (Debt – Cash), Minority interest, Preferred stock.\r\n2.1.7 Common DCF Mistakes & Fixes (Negative FCF → reassess model, Unrealistic growth or margin assumptions, Forgetting\r\nto match year-end conventions, Over-relying on Terminal Value.\r\n2.2 Comparable Company Analysis (Comps)\r\n2.2.1 Purpose of Comps - Why use comparables, When to use it, Pros & Cons vs. DCF and precedent transactions.\r\n2.2.2 Selecting Comparable Companies - Criteria for Comparability (Industry, Size, Geography, Growth profile & Margins).\r\nSource for identifying comps (Capital IQ, PitchBook, Refinitiv, 10-Ks, investor presentations)\r\nMO2.2.3\r\nFinancial Normalization & Adjustments - Adjust for one-time/non-recurring items in income statements, Remove\r\nextraordinary gains/losses, Normalize EBITDA for clean comparison, Convert financials to a common currency/time\r\nperiod if needed.\r\n2.2.4 Calculating Enterprise Value\r\n2.2.5 Key Valuation Multiples to Study - Enterprise Value-based Multiples (EV), Equity Value-based Multiples.\r\n2.2.6 Creating a Comparable Universe Table, Interpreting Multiples, Applying the Multiples to your Target.\r\n2.2.7 Common Pitfalls & Best Practices - Avoiding cherry-picking comps, Adjusting for non-comparable financials, Keeping\r\nsource data up to date, Consistency in accounting basis and fiscal year.\r\n2.3 Precedent Transaction Analysis (PTA)\r\n2.3.1 Purpose of PTA - What is PTA, Why it\'s used, Pros & Cons\r\n2.3.2 Selecting the Right Precedent Deals - Criteria and Sources\r\n2.3.3 Key Deal Metrics - Transaction Value (EV), Financials at Deal Time, Premium Paid\r\n2.3.4 Valuation Multiples to Use (EV / EBITDA, EV / Revenue, Equity Value / Net Income)\r\n2.3.5 Making Adjustments - Normalize Financials, Adjust for Changes in Accounting Standards, Convert to a consistent\r\ncurrency/timeframe\r\n2.3.6 Building the Transaction Comp Table, Applying the Multiples, Output Presentation\r\n2.3.7 Risks & Best Practices - Deal Timing (e.g. Crisis year deals), Don\'t Mix Industries / Structures, Control Premiums\r\nvary widely, Document all deal sources', '2025-05-31 15:33:35', '2025-05-31 15:33:35'),
(49, 61, 2, 'Advanced Deal Structuring', '1 Corporate Finance & Capital Markets\r\n1.1 Corporate Finance\r\n1.1.1 Cost of Capital - WACC (Weighted Average Cost of Capital), Cost of Equity, Cost of Debt, Optimal Capital Structure\r\n(Impact on WACC, ROE, and Risk)\r\n1.1.2 Capital Structure - Components (Common Equity, Preferred Stock, Short/Long term debt), Leverage Ratios, Capital\r\nStructure Theories, Debt vs Equity Financing\r\n1.1.3 Working Capital - Net Working Capital, Cash conversion Cycle, Liquidity and Efficiency Ratios, Impact on Valuation\r\n1.2 Capital Markets\r\n1.2.1 Initial Public Offerings (IPOs) - IPO Process, Valuation Approaches, Post-IPO Performance Metrics\r\n1.2.2 Bonds (Debt Capital Markets) - Types of Bonds, Bond Terms, Bond Pricing, Credit Ratings & Risk\r\n1.2.3 Equity Markets - Primary vs Secondary Markets, Stock Valuation Basics, Institutional Participation, Stock Market\r\nIndices, Trading Mechanisms\r\n2 Mergers & Acquisitions (M&A) Modeling\r\n2.1 M&A Deal Structures - Types of M&A (Horizontal, Vertical, Conglomerate), Deal Considerations (Friendly vs. Hostile\r\nTakeover, Asset vs. Stock Purchase, All-Cash, All-Stock, or Mixed Consideration)\r\n2.2 Key M&A Concepts - Synergies (Revenue, Cost, How to estimate & model them), Control Premium & Minority Interest,\r\nGoodwill, Purchase Price Allocation.\r\n2.3 Building the M&A Model - Step by Step Process\r\n2.4 Key Metrics - Pro Forma EPS, Leverage, Return on Invested Capital, Debt service coverage after deal, etc.\r\n2.5 Sensitivity & Scenario Analysis - Synergy levels (low vs high), Purchase Multiples, Deal Structure\r\n2.6 Deal Evaluation & Best Practices - Strategic Rationale for Acquisition, Risks & Integration Issues, Antitrust, Shareholder\r\nimpact on market reaction, Build error checks, Summary Outputs, Clear Color Coding\r\n3 Leveraged Buyouts (LBO) Modeling\r\n3.1 Definition, Goals, Why LBO?, Sources of Funds, and Uses of Funds.\r\n3.2 Key LBO Concepts - Leverage Ratio, Interest Coverage Ratio, Minimum Cash Balance, Cash Sweep, Exit Assumptions.\r\n3.3 Building the LBO Model - Step by Step Process\r\n3.4 Key Metrics - Entry and Exit Multiples, IRR, MOIC, Leverage Ratios, Cash Flow available for Debt Service.\r\n3.5 Sensitivity & Scenario Analysis - Vary Exit Multiples, Revenue Growth, EBITDA Margins, Holding Period, IRR Heat Maps\r\n3.6 Best Practices and Bonus Concepts - Dividend Recaps, Management Rollover Equity, Warrants & Convertible Instruments,\r\nError Checks, Dynamic Debt Repayment Logic.\r\n4 Synergies, Accretion/Dilution Analysis\r\n4.1 Understanding Synergies - Types of Synergies (Revenue Synergies, Cost Synergies, Tax Synergies, Operational Synergies\r\n4.2 Accretion/Dilution Analysis - Accretive, Dilutive, Neutral, Pro Forma Net Income, Pro Forma Shares Outstanding, Pro Forma\r\nEPS, Comparison (Pre-deal EPS and Post-deal EPS)\r\n4.3 Deal Financing Impact - All Cash Deal, All Stock Deal, Mixed Deal\r\n4.4 Sensitivity Analysis - Purchase Price, Interest Rate on Debt, Synergy Levels, Stock Price Volatility.\r\n4.5 Best Practices - Accretion/Dilution Bridge in Excel, EPS Sensitivity Tables, Use clear formatting and Color coding.', '2025-05-31 15:33:35', '2025-05-31 15:33:35'),
(50, 61, 2, 'Financial and Visualization Tools for Investment Bankers', '1 Capital IQ (S&P Global)\r\n1.1 Platform Navigation & Interface - Understanding the tool\r\n1.2 Company Profile Analysis - Business overview & description, Industry Classification (GICS, SIC, NAICS), Ownership\r\nstructure, segment reporting.\r\n1.3 Financial Statements & Ratios - Compare Income Statement, Balance Sheet, and Cash Flow statements of multiple companies\r\nside by side.\r\n1.4 Excel Plugin & Formula Builder - Install CIQ Excel Plugin, Pull live data into Excel. Automate Financial Models like DCF,\r\nComps, Football Field Charts, etc.\r\n1.5 Comparable Company Analysis - Screen & Select peers based on Sector, Region, Financial Metrics\r\n1.6 Precedent Transaction - Historical M&A Deals based on Deal Size, Geography, Target Type.\r\n1.7 Debt & Equity Capital Markets Activity\r\n1.8 Analyst Estimates & Forecasts - EPS and revenue, Consensus Valuation, Forward Multiples\r\n1.9 News, filings, and Documents\r\n2 Bloomberg Terminal\r\n2.1 Basics & Navigation - Login Interface, Terminal Layout, and Common Shortcuts\r\n2.2 Company Financials & Valuation - FA, DES, EE\r\n2.3 Comparable Company Analysis - RV, GP\r\n2.4 Precedent Transactions & Deal Screening - MA, DVMT\r\n2.5 Debt Market & Bond Analysis - CACS, CRPR, YAS\r\n2.6 Equity Market Tools - WEI, BETA, HP\r\n2.7 News & Macro Data - TOP, ECON, SURP, RATE\r\n2.8 Excel Integration - Bloomberg Excel Add-in, Linking for Real Time Data, Build Real time dashboards and pitchbook visuals.\r\n3 Refinitiv Eikon\r\n3.1 Platform Navigation & Dashboard Setup\r\n3.2 Company Financials & Profiles\r\n3.3 Valuation Multiples & Peer Comparison\r\n3.4 M&A and Deal Screening (Precedent Transactions)\r\n3.5 Debt & Equity Capital Markets\r\n3.6 Macroeconomic Data & Market Indicators - Monitor Indices, Economic Releases, Commodities, Currencies, and Interest Rate\r\nForecasts.\r\n3.7 Excel Integration with Refinitiv Add-In - Automating Dashboards, Pull Live or Static financial data.\r\n3.8 News, Transcripts & Filings\r\n3.9 IB-Specific Use Cases\r\n4 Tableau\r\n4.1 Basic Tableau Skills - Navigating Tableau Interface, Connecting different data sources, Data Types, Fields, and Hierarchies.\r\nCleaning & preparing data, Sorting Filtering, and grouping data\r\n4.2 Working with Financial Data - Importing financial statements, Multi-year revenue and profit visualizations, Year-over-year\r\ngrowth analysis.\r\n4.3 Basic Visualizations - Line, Bar, Pie, Area, and Scatter Plots.\r\n4.4 Advanced Visualizations - Waterfall Charts, Bullet Charts, Gantt Charts, Dual-Axis Charts, Scatter Plot with Trendline.\r\n4.5 Dashboards & Storytelling - Pitchbook Style Dashboard, Investor updates, Deal summaries\r\n4.6 Mapping - Heatmaps by Geography, Geographical revenue segmentation\r\n4.7 Integration with Excel Models - Connect Tableau to Excel based financial Models, Auto refresh charts when Excel updates\r\ndata.\r\n5 Power BI\r\n5.1 Power BI Basics - Understanding Interface, connecting to Excel, CSV, SQL, Web. Data types, fields, and modeling basics.\r\nData Cleaning using Power Query Editor\r\n5.2 Importing & Structuring Financial Data - Importing financial statements, creating relationship models, structuring data for\r\nfinancial dashboards, DAX, EBITDA Margin, Net profit Margin, ROE, ROA, Debt-to-Equity, etc.\r\n5.3 Creating Financial Dashboards - Revenue & EBITDA Trends, Peer Comparison Dashboards, Capital structure Visualizations,\r\nFree Cash Flow Waterfall.\r\n5.4 Advanced Visualization - KPI Cards, Bar Charts, Waterfall Charts, Heatmaps, Gantt Chart\r\n5.5 Dashboard Filters and Interactivity\r\n5.6 Live Data and Integration - Schedule refreshes from Excel/SQL Databases, Connect to APIs, Export Visuals for Pitchbook\r\n5.7 Investor Focused Reporting - IPO Deal Pipeline, Fund performance over time, M&A Activity, Shareholder Analysis.', '2025-05-31 15:33:35', '2025-05-31 15:33:35'),
(51, 61, 2, 'Basic Python for Automation', '1\r\nPython Fundamentals - Variables, Data Types, Operators & Expressions, Control Statements (IF, ELSE, ELIF), Loops (FOR,\r\nWHILE), Functions (def, return values, arguments)\r\n2 Working with Financial Data (PANDAS) - Importing Data (CSV/EXCEL), Data Wrangling & Manipulation (Filtering, sorting, grouping,\r\nmerging datasets, creating calculated fields, Time Series Data\r\n3\r\nAutomation Use Cases - Cleaning & Formatting Excel Files (Automate Repetitive formatting, Consolidate multiple Excel sheets into\r\none, rename columns, remove null values, validate values. Extract key items like revenue, EBITDA, Net income from CSV & EXCEL\r\nfiles\r\n4 Web Scraping for Financial Data - Requests & BeautifulSoup to pull stock prices from websites, scrape valuation multiples\r\n5 Data Visualization using Matplotlib and Seaborn - Line, Bar, Heatmaps, Scatterplot, Waterfall chart.\r\n6 Excel Automation with OpenPyXL / XlsxWriter\r\n7 Build a Mini Project - DCF Calculator in Python / Automated Comps Table Generator / Stock Screener / Excel Report Generator for\r\nM&A Deals.', '2025-05-31 15:33:35', '2025-05-31 15:33:35'),
(52, 61, 2, 'Professional Soft Skills, Pitchbook, & IB Deliverables', '1 Pitchbook\r\n1.1 What\'s a Pitchbook? Purpose of Pitchbook, Who\'s it for?\r\n1.2 Types of Pitchbooks - Company Pitch (Profiling & Positioning), Sell-Side M&A Pitch, Buy-Side Mandate Pitch, IPO/Equity\r\nOffering Deck, Strategic Alternatives Overview, Fairness Opinions & Valuation Presentations.\r\n1.3 Sections and Index of a Standard Pitchbook\r\n1.4 Company Profiling & Investor Decks - What to include in a Company Profile, Visual Storytelling, Investor Deck Focus.\r\n1.5 Creation Tools & Standards - Microsoft PowerPoint, Integration with Excel Models & Charts. Using data from Capital IQ,\r\nBloomberg, and company filings.\r\n1.6 Deal Presentation Strategies and Best Practices\r\n1.7 Miscellaneous - Build a Football Field Chart, Precedent deal tombstones, Modular Decks\r\n2 Professional Soft Skills\r\n2.1 Introduction to Soft Skills & Self Introduction Techniques\r\n2.2 Effective Communication\r\n2.3 SWOT Analysis (Self Assessment)\r\n2.4 Email Writing for Corporates\r\n2.5 Group Discussion Techniques & Teamwork\r\n2.6 Time Management & Negotiation Skills\r\n2.7 Resume Building & Vetting\r\n2.8 Grooming Tips & Professional Etiquette\r\n2.9 Interview Tips & Techniques + Mock Interviews', '2025-05-31 15:33:35', '2025-05-31 15:33:35');
